                                                                    <h4><em><a href="/">Journal of Management Information Systems</a></em></h4>
                                                                
        
    <div><a href="/issues/12">    Volume 2 Number 1 1985
</a> pp. 39-60</div>
                                
                                    <div class="margin-bottom-5">
        <h3>Classifying An Organization to Identify Its Information Requirements: A Comprehensive Framework</h3>
    </div>
    <div class="margin-bottom-10">
            <a href="/contributors/1622">Yadav, Surya B</a>    </div>

<p>ABSTRACT: This paper presents a methodological framework for classifying organizations in order to identify their information requirements. The framework is in the form of guidelines to study and characterize an organization, starting from a broad vantage point and continuing on to a detailed analysis of specific managerial actions. The methodology was applied to study a city government and a medium-sized bank, with encouraging results.</p>

    <strong>Key words and phrases: </strong>
        <a href="/keywords/89">information in organizations</a>,    <a href="/keywords/90">organization design</a>,    <a href="/keywords/91">system analysis</a>,    <a href="/keywords/92">analysis methodologies</a>,    <a href="/keywords/93">information requirements</a>
                                
                        
